This analysis covers South Africaâ€™s performance in global cricket tournaments from the 1990s. Included are all ICC tournaments â€” ODI and T20 World Cups, Champions Trophies, and World Test Championship cycles â€” as well as a few quadrangular tournaments from the 1990s that involved at least four Test-playing nations. A total of 33 tournaments were considered. Each tournament was assigned a performance score based on the stage reached. For major ICC events, the scale was: 5 for a title win, 4 for final, 3 for semi-final, 2 for quarter-final, and 1 for group-stage exit. In the case of the 90s quadrangular series, the scores were downgraded by one point per stage to reflect their lesser stature. Additional variables such as year, tournament name, exit opponent, match margin, and captain are used to explore trends over time and captaincy tenures.
